On Nov 11, 2003, at 3:47 PM, Billy wrote:

> Bingo! Terminal 50 is battery power no matter where you are in the 
> bus. Any circuit that connects directly to the battery will do so via 
> a Terminal labeled "50".  Your cable from the battery connects to the 
> solenoid directly, not the starter. Look at your wiring diagram, is 
> the hot side of the battery labeled "50"?

No, I think that's "30" :-)  (See Richard's reply to my message.)

> Ever notice the "15" on your coil?  Isn't there a "30" on the 
> solenoid?  Hmmmm.

"30" on the solenoid comes from the battery, and "50" on the solenoid 
is the signal  from the starter switch.

